{
  "stem": "19550.8",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe I was in the middle of telling that this is, that the Holocaust story is going to be the longest untold story ever told.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I am quite convinced that that will be the case.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, perhaps my own concentration camp career, if you would forgive me for the expression, can be an illustration of one aspect of this inexpressibility of the camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean you take me, I was fundamentally incarcerated for exactly one year.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In one year, I went to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I went through France in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went from there through the better part of Germany, through Kochendorf, Heilbronn am Neckar, Dachau, and finally [INAUDIBLE], and then was still presumably being transported to a place that was rumored to be [INAUDIBLE] in Austria, where we were all supposed to have been either shot or drowned into a lake, so that no trace of us would be left.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the things experienced, learned, and the things done or not done, felt and thought, would take my whole life, not the years that I have left, but the years I have lived already, to describe.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then I would not come nearly to the point where I will have adequately described what I had gone through.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this has really nothing to do with whether or not I was beaten, or whether I was driven.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It's the life of one year and of six camps is, each moment of it was an eternity.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Finally, as I said before, we were shuttled to the Tutzing and were liberated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And unlike I suppose 99 and 9, 99% of the survivors, I had an address.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When we were deported, we all of course etched into our heart and into our mind our father's, sister's address where he had lived.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
